1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,200
Two strangers.

2
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:07,840
Bound by pain.

3
00:00:08,120 --> 00:00:09,120
By destiny, by fate.

4
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:12,040
Ateş.

5
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:14,640
A man who returned with fire in his heart

6
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,680
and revenge in his hands.

7
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:18,800
Mercan.

8
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,720
A girl trapped in a story she never chose.

9
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:25,000
Yet brave enough to believe in love.

10
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,960
From the very beginning, there was anger.

11
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,640
Distance, silence.

12
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,880
Wounds too deep for words to describe...

13
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:16,320
It all began with a contract.

14
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:18,080
A forced marriage.

15
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:22,040
Bound by a promise that
would end the day it hurt.

16
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:24,400
And it became something
neither of them could escape.

17
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,560
Because between hatred and heartbreak,

18
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,800
Between pride and longing...

19
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:31,840
Two hearts began to change.

20
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:36,040
Eyes that once avoided
each other began to search for one another.

21
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:39,680
Words that once broke began to heal.

22
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:19,120
And
love slowly, dangerously, began to blossom.

23
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:21,840
But love never comes alone.

24
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:24,320
It came with secrets,
it came with betrayal.

25
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:27,760
And with
a past that refused to stay buried.

26
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,760
You lived this story with them.

27
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:35,400
Every day, every
wound, every fall, every impossible choice.

28
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,640
This is not just the end of a story.

29
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:42,240
This is the moment when love, pain,
and destiny finally come face to face.

30
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:47,760
And now, for one last
time, witness this moment of truth.

31
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,696
As you seek the answer
to a single question.

32
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:53,640
Can love truly survive even in Arafta?

33
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:47,160
Good morning!

34
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,480
Well look at you, the bride’s already up.

35
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,159
I couldn’t get a proper wink of sleep.

36
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,760
I was so worked up, you have no idea.

37
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,800
I
Can tell, it’s written all over your face.

38
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,680
But why are you acting like this, Mercan?

39
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,160
Anyway, we’ll do
a little skincare or something now.

40
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,960
What’s wrong with my face?

41
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,960
You look pale. Go wash your face first.

42
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:14,760
Come on.

43
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:17,120
Oh please. Is that so?

44
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,880
Oh,
the groom’s awake. Feeling good like this?

45
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:45,576
You’d think I’m the one getting married.
Get up, it’s your wedding day.

46
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:47,880
Morning, brother. Big day today. Ready?

47
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,920
I’ve been ready for this day for
a long time.

48
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:58,320
Ever since
you first saw Mercan, right? That’s my lad.

49
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:02,959
Only thing is, brother, your heart’s ready…

50
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,200
…maybe you should get yourself ready on the
outside too?

51
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,039
Not that you need anything.

52
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,520
It’s
just how it goes. A shave, getting dressed.

53
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,480
Come on, up you go, we’ve got a lot to do.

54
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,279
We’ll get it all done, don’t worry.

55
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:15,200
But first, I need to see Mercan.

56
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,000
Whoa, not so fast, brother.

57
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,920
It’s tradition, they won’t allow it.

58
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,640
You can’t see the bride until the wedding.

59
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:26,000
Come on, man, don’t exaggerate.

60
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,560
Good morning.

61
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,440
I missed you so much.

62
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,360
I’ll be right there, wait for me.

63
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,400
Hold on, hold on.

64
00:06:58,280 --> 00:06:59,280
We’ve been taken hostage.

65
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,320
You look beautiful.

66
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,640
Really?

67
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,680
Because Demet doesn’t seem to agree.

68
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,080
I couldn’t sleep, that’s why.

69
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,680
Then Demet must be mistaken.

70
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,120
I’m so nervous.

71
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:24,640
Me too.

72
00:07:24,641 --> 00:07:26,120
It feels like…

73
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,920
…my heart’s about to leap out of my chest.

74
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,120
Easy now, my pearl, my Mercan.

75
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,560
Today is our day.

76
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,560
Day 187.

77
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,600
The first day of our new life.

78
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,640
After everything we’ve been through…

79
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,680
…we deserve a celebration like this.

80
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:50,840
I love you so much.

81
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,280
I love you too.

82
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,760
I should hang up and get ready now.

83
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,200
I’m heading out, Cemal.

84
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,480
Where to?

85
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:25,080
There’s somewhere I need to visit.

86
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,680
I’ll change and head out.

87
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,400
Alright, brother.

88
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:45,960
Feels like the first day you opened
your hearts to each other, doesn’t it?

89
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,000
Is it that obvious?

90
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,079
Demet…

91
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:54,040
I fall for him more every single day.

92
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,520
There’s nothing better in this world.

93
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,840
And Mercan, you deserve every bit of it.

94
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,160
What’s going on?

95
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:10,120
Why are you still wandering around in your
pajamas?

96
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,160
This early in the morning…

97
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,480
With ten hours left until the wedding…

98
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,720
Shame on us.

99
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:20,440
Time slips through your fingers before you
even notice.

100
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:22,440
Come on now, move it.

101
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,000
Mercan, go get dressed right away.

102
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:26,080
Demet, you check our lists.

103
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,120
This will be the wedding of the year.

104
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,160
I want everything flawless, understood?

105
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,440
Come on, girls, get moving.

106
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,640
Go, go, go.

107
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:44,200
Keep your eyes and ears on me.

108
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:47,040
I’ll
wait for the right moment and let you know.

109
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,040
Alright.

110
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:51,960
I’ve already prepared everything.

111
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:57,200
I planned a beautiful surprise for them.

112
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,400
Don’t you dare forget what I said.

113
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,400
Do whatever you want with Mercan.

114
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:08,360
Hold her close or send her to hell for all
I care.

115
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,720
But as for Ateş…

116
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,280
…you will not touch him.

117
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:17,000
Don’t worry, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

118
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:20,160
I’m only here to take back what’s mine.

119
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,120
I have no business with Ateş.

120
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:38,320
From this point on, Ateş’s
business is with the grave.

121
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:41,680
He’ll sleep there in peace.

122
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:50,880
Brother…

123
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:54,280
I came without bringing Mercan.

124
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,600
She wouldn’t be able
to bear it, she’d get emotional.

125
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,680
But I know seeing us makes you happy.

126
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,760
I set out on this
path driven by revenge and pain…

127
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,760
…and reached an ending I never expected.

128
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,960
You would have wanted this too.

129
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,160
Not evil, but goodness.

130
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,240
Not hatred, but love.

131
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,040
Mercan…

132
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,840
She healed me with her miracle.

133
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,480
Just like my loneliness, those 187 days are
over.

134
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,360
I won’t be fighting those
storms alone anymore.

135
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,560
I won’t be walking those thorny paths…

136
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,480
…on my own anymore.

137
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:58,520
I’m stronger now, more
at peace than before.

138
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,880
Once, there was nothing for me but death.

139
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:10,359
Now, even if something is missing…

140
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,520
…a new life is beginning.

141
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:35,360
I swore on this bracelet…

142
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:45,800
…that I’d change everything in 187 days.

143
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,840
Yes.

144
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,560
Everything has changed.

145
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,360
Just the way you would have wanted.

146
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:05,200
Your brother
chose goodness, not evil, Eylül.

147
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:13,960
He chose happiness.

148
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,440
I love you so much, Eylül.

149
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,320
I love you so much.

150
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,640
I need to get
out of here as soon as possible.

151
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,960
That bastard
Nezir is going to hand me over to Müzeyyen.

152
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:22,280
Müzeyyen won’t let me live.

153
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:01,800
You’re a smart man.

154
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,400
This is small work for you.

155
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,320
Meaning?

156
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:10,720
You’re capable of more than just guarding
Müzeyyen.

157
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:12,440
Especially if there’s money involved.

158
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:19,240
Help me, and I’ll pay you double.

159
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:21,921
Then you won’t
have to crawl at the feet of dogs anymore.

160
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,400
Easy work, guys.

161
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,800
Put that over there, brother.

162
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,600
Looks great, honestly.

163
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:46,160
Bring the flowers,
brother, bring them. Let’s spread them out.

164
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,480
Let’s cover this one too. There’s fabric
over there.

165
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:08,920
Mom?

166
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:10,680
Where were you?

167
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:13,760
Nowhere, I just wandered outside a bit.

168
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:18,520
This place is pretty much in order now.

169
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:22,080
If you hadn’t stepped in, I don’t know how
I’d have managed.

170
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,280
It was good for me too.

171
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:26,560
Kept me busy for a while.

172
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,880
I wanted to do something, but…

173
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:31,880
…Ateş and Mercan wouldn’t allow it.

174
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,560
It’s fine.

175
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,760
We’ll tell them after the wedding anyway.

176
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:38,680
Maybe Ateş will soften toward you.

177
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:40,960
Maybe.

178
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,880
It’s not that important.

179
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,400
It’s fine if he never knows.

180
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,520
As long as it doesn’t
stay bottled up inside me.

181
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,000
How are you?

182
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,880
I’ll be better after today.

183
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:00,840
We’re slowly healing our wounds.

184
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:05,040
This one stayed right here.

185
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,840
Every time I visit my son’s grave…

186
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:09,680
…I rub the soil onto my wound.

187
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:11,680
Not so it heals…

188
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,320
…but so it burns even more.

189
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,440
So it burns, so I never forget my enemies.

190
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,320
Mom, don’t.

191
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:22,760
Alright, my girl.

192
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,160
Don’t you worry.

193
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:27,120
Look,
you’re here, you’re with me, you’re well.

194
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,000
Everything will get better.

195
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,320
Let today pass first.

196
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,320
Nothing will happen, right?

197
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,376
Brother, you finally made
it, I’ve been waiting.

198
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,599
We’ve got a ton to do, I swear.

199
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:03,840
And you’re still stalling.

200
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:10,160
Who are these guys?
Where did you find them?

201
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:12,920
Them… Müzeyyen
took care of it. No problem, don’t worry.

202
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,680
They said Haydar and Nezir fled abroad.

203
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:18,760
But you never know with
men like them, Cemal.

204
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,760
Let’s keep security tight.

205
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:23,600
We will, brother, we will.

206
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:27,760
But today you’re not the boss, you’re the
groom.

207
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:29,799
A man becomes a groom once in a lifetime.

208
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:33,280
Forget everything today, you can take over
tomorrow.

209
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,240
Besides, the groom’s shave awaits us.

210
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,960
You’re
in charge, Cemal. Do whatever’s necessary.

211
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:43,520
I want today to be flawless for Mercan.

212
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,440
It will be, for both of you.

213
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,120
Well, look
at that, you’re becoming a groom.

214
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,720
Why don’t you step out onto the balcony?

215
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,440
Mercan?

216
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:33,720
Ateş…

217
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:32,000
Come on, Mercan, come on.

218
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:42,200
Come on, brother, we’ve
got a long day ahead, let’s go.

219
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,680
We can’t leave it like this. Take it easy.

220
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,200
Let’s do it in a bun.

221
00:20:55,960 --> 00:21:00,920
Or maybe leave it down like this… I’m not
sure.

222
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:06,520
I don’t even know what I want yet.

223
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:11,016
How are we supposed to make it on
time if we can’t even decide on your hair?

224
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:14,320
That’s what happens when you leave it
to the last day. I told you to do a trial.

225
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,079
A hair trial? Seriously?

226
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:17,120
Of course.

227
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:23,160
Alright, we’ll handle
it. Just leave yourself to me now, okay?

228
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:37,560
It looks beautiful.

229
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:54,760
Hell!

230
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,120
Where’s Haydar?

231
00:21:58,960 --> 00:21:59,960
Where is he, damn it?

232
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:02,280
I…

233
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,360
Where is Haydar?

234
00:22:04,361 --> 00:22:05,680
Speak!

235
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:09,880
I saw him
talking about the plan on the phone, boss.

236
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:12,920
He’s the one who let Haydar go.

237
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:15,000
Haydar was heading to the mansion.

238
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:24,600
Move!

239
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,320
No one’s going to ruin my plan!

240
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:40,160
Move!

241
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:48,000
Hold
it, son, hold it. There, fix that spot too.

242
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:50,920
Let me see.

243
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:55,360
Looks great.

244
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,440
May it be your turn
next with Çiçek and Malik, Insallah.

245
00:22:58,560 --> 00:22:59,440
Insallah.

246
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:02,959
Amen, Mother Binnaz, amen.

247
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,720
Amen, of course, brother.

248
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:05,800
Brother.

249
00:23:05,801 --> 00:23:07,280
These look good too, huh.

250
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:10,160
No, you’re not eating.
Nothing gets touched.

251
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:15,440
What are you doing?

252
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,080
Girl, leave those alone, for God’s sake.

253
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:19,079
Goodness gracious, goodness gracious.

254
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:20,319
My dear wife…

255
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:24,360
You’re pregnant! And look at you, running around
like this… You’ll just sit and watch today.

256
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:25,440
You’re not doing a thing.

257
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:27,400
But I want to help.

258
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:31,120
We’re all here, everyone’s already doing
their part.

259
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:33,120
You’ll sit down and not tire yourself out.

260
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:35,000
Mother Binnaz is right, Zehra.

261
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:36,360
Don’t strain yourself.

262
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:39,440
What if you fall ill at our wedding…

263
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,800
God forbid.

264
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,560
The expert speaks, brother.

265
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:52,520
We set the date for our
wedding two weeks from now.

266
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,560
Oh… thank God.

267
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,480
Good news keeps coming one after another.

268
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:03,160
Oh, my beautiful girl.

269
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,896
May it be
blessed and bring you happiness, Insallah.

270
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:05,720
Thanks, Mother Binnaz.

271
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,040
Thank you, my dear mother.

272
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:11,920
If I hadn’t given permission, you wouldn’t
be getting married.

273
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:15,680
Oh, may God bless you, brother.

274
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,880
Well, brother, I was thinking…

275
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:21,480
What would we have done without you?

276
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:24,520
I really don’t know.

277
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,800
Go on, make fun of me.

278
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,680
Don’t make me switch into big brother mode.

279
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,040
No, don’t.

280
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:32,200
May it be blessed.

281
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:34,720
Thank you, Zehra.

282
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,040
Thank you, Zehra.

283
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:40,800
I mean…

284
00:24:40,801 --> 00:24:45,360
I wish my mother hadn’t left. If she were
here, everything would feel better.

285
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:48,800
Right when a grandchild is on the way too.

286
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:52,240
Alright, enough chatter.

287
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,680
We’ve still got
a lot to do, all these tables need setting.

288
00:24:55,040 --> 00:24:55,720
Zehra, you sit down.

289
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:58,000
You two go inside and bring everything out.

290
00:24:58,080 --> 00:24:59,920
You left things half done.

291
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:02,800
Right when a grandchild is coming, no less.

292
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:05,000
You stay here, I’ll bring you a chair.

293
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:06,080
Still talking.

294
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,520
Brother, today’s a big day for me too.

295
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:23,319
I’m thinking I should come clean today.

296
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:26,280
I’ll go and say,
“This is how I feel,” and be done with it.

297
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,040
That would suit you.

298
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,520
I wish you had done it earlier.

299
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:33,240
We could’ve had a double wedding.

300
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,840
Come on, brother,
for God’s sake, we’ve got a long day ahead.

301
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,040
Sit.

302
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,960
Today, you’re in my care, brother.

303
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:47,280
I won’t entrust you to anyone else.

304
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:48,960
Not on a day like this.

305
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:51,520
I’ll get you ready with my own hands.

306
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:56,920
Mr. Groom, if you’re ready, we’ll begin.

307
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,200
Cemal is a good man, of course.

308
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:07,360
I don’t know…

309
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:08,160
It’s hard.

310
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:09,800
You know it too.

311
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:12,360
Look what you
went through before you could even say it.

312
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,200
It’s not easy, of course.

313
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:23,359
Actually…

314
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:24,360
Never mind.

315
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,000
How would it even work anyway?

316
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:28,440
Everything’s out in the open.

317
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:33,560
If one step is taken,
the rest will come crashing in.

318
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:35,800
Forget about me for now.

319
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:37,720
Today is your day, let’s not lose focus.

320
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:39,760
Let’s get you ready as soon as possible.

321
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:44,880
We’ll leave you two alone.

322
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,200
I hurt you so much, my daughter.

323
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:07,560
They say the one who
cries the most deserves to smile the most.

324
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,720
That’s how it turned out for you.

325
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,600
From now on,
you’ll always smile, I know it.

326
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,640
I wish we could’ve all been together.

327
00:29:22,480 --> 00:29:25,640
I wish
your brother and your father were here too.

328
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,040
I wish we had managed to be a family.

329
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:35,760
I wish, my daughter. I wish.

330
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,480
We failed to be a family.

331
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:43,200
But you and Ateş will succeed.

332
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:45,480
Enough tears now.

333
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,160
You’ll ruin your makeup.

334
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,000
Alright.

335
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,760
I love you so much, my daughter.

336
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:52,880
Come here.

337
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,520
I love you too, Mom.

338
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:07,920
I won’t cry.

339
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:10,800
This time, I’ll listen to my mother.

340
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:15,040
Then let’s get you ready.

341
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,880
Put on your wedding dress. Come on.

342
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:22,520
Demet?

343
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:47,920
Peace be upon you.

344
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:49,960
Peace be upon you.

345
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,560
And peace be upon you.

346
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,280
And peace be upon you.

347
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:56,280
We gave our hearts, we gave our word.

348
00:30:58,600 --> 00:31:00,440
We gave our hearts, we gave our word.

349
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:02,600
We’ve come to take the bride.

350
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:04,480
We’ve come to take the bride.

351
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:11,280
Let the drums roar, let the ground shake.

352
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:13,680
Let the whole world hear us. Hit the drum,
old man!

353
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:13,800
My girl must look like a swan already.

354
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:20,040
She’s coming, she’s coming.

355
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:42,479
She looks so beautiful…

356
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,759
Oh, my beauty.

357
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:45,760
May God grant you happiness.

358
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,520
You look stunning, my daughter.

359
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,920
Mercan, you look beautiful.

360
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:04,040
I came into your life too late.

361
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:19,720
Maybe I wasn’t there in your dark days…

362
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:25,280
But I stood by you in your happiest ones.

363
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,200
Be happy for a lifetime, my sister.

364
00:34:46,640 --> 00:34:48,720
Are you ready for your new life?

365
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:10,840
Let me do this…

366
00:35:34,320 --> 00:35:37,840
Oh, the door’s heavy. It won’t open.

367
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:42,360
I’ve got it, brother.

368
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:09,400
Let me
check. No, it still won’t open, Mr. Cemal.

369
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,520
Look, I swear it’s not working.

370
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:14,080
Brother, they say it still won’t open. What
do we do?

371
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:18,200
Anything beautiful is
worth the wait, brother.

372
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:26,280
We accept the thorns and the whims alike.

373
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,360
As long as it ends in joy.

374
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,160
Then please, go ahead.

375
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:17,360
My sister is entrusted to you, Ateş.

376
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,600
What’s entrusted to me
is dearer than my life.

377
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:27,840
My love is entrusted to you, your heart is
entrusted to me.

378
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:36,120
I’ll stand by you for a lifetime. My heart
is yours.

379
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:04,880
Let tradition be
fulfilled, let there be abundance.

380
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:18,640
Message received. You’re
the head of the family.

381
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:29,040
Right. Wait, Mom. Here,
take it. Alright then.

382
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:34,920
Let’s not keep the guests waiting.

383
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:41,200
Ateş, my hands and feet are shaking.
I feel like I might fall any moment.

384
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:44,080
If you fall, I’ll catch you.

385
00:40:44,560 --> 00:40:47,920
I know you will,
but I don’t want to be the bride who falls.

386
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:53,320
That would be something. We’d have stories
to tell our children.

387
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:57,160
Sure,
they’d say, “Our mother was so clumsy.”

388
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:00,840
The clumsiest mother in the world.

389
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:48,040
I’m so happy. But this kind of happiness
feels like it only exists in dreams.

390
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:52,880
I’m afraid of waking up.

391
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:59,120
Our dreams and our
reality will both be filled with happiness.

392
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:03,360
Your husband promises
you a lifetime of happiness.

393
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:16,240
Demet, would you dance with me?

394
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:34,680
Shall we dance too, Zahide?

395
00:42:36,160 --> 00:42:37,160
Sure.

396
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:41,360
Alright.

397
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:43,360
So…

398
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:48,560
Mercan and the others will go on
their honeymoon after the wedding.

399
00:42:49,240 --> 00:42:51,920
The job in Italy will
fall to me. I’ll fly out after the wedding.

400
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:55,120
I
Can speak to them for you too, if you want.

401
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:58,120
[ITALIAN WORDS]

402
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:02,840
Sorry, my mind drifted to Italy from
excitement. It’s always the excitement.

403
00:43:03,600 --> 00:43:06,600
Speak up, Zahide.
Have them take me too. Let’s go together.

404
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:09,080
Let’s go eat gelato in
Rome. Real Roman gelato.

405
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:12,520
Let’s have tiramisu. We’ll
go to the Fountain of Love and make a wish.

406
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:13,960
We’ll make an album.

407
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:15,280
Alright, sure. Go on, say it.

408
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:47,240
Everyone’s looking at us.

409
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:52,040
But I only see you.

410
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:56,840
It feels like the world
has stopped and only we are moving.

411
00:43:58,480 --> 00:44:00,440
If you’re tired…

412
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:17,159
I was actually today…

413
00:44:17,160 --> 00:44:18,160
Yes?

414
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:19,800
Today…

415
00:44:22,320 --> 00:44:23,960
The weather is beautiful today, isn’t it?

416
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:26,400
Yes.

417
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:33,440
It’s beautiful when people
in love come together, isn’t it?

418
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:37,200
Cemal…

419
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:38,599
I…

420
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:39,600
You?

421
00:44:43,320 --> 00:44:44,560
I’m so happy for them.

422
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:47,440
They suit each other so well, don’t they?

423
00:44:47,560 --> 00:44:49,320
They really do.

424
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,440
Whatever happens, happens.

425
00:44:54,080 --> 00:44:55,400
Demet, I…

426
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:22,040
Uncle Durmuş…

427
00:45:22,760 --> 00:45:24,040
Mashallah, mashallah.

428
00:45:24,280 --> 00:45:25,600
Mashallah, my girl, mashallah.

429
00:45:25,640 --> 00:45:27,880
We’re so happy to see you.

430
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:29,760
So are we, my child.

431
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:35,520
You’ve thought of everything so
beautifully, children. Mashallah.

432
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:41,160
I was thinking…

433
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:43,680
Should we renew our vows, my Güllü?

434
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:46,000
Oh, come on now…

435
00:45:48,720 --> 00:45:50,840
Is that something to do at our age?

436
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,560
Go tend to your guests.

437
00:45:59,680 --> 00:46:00,680
Mashallah.

438
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:32,200
Come on?

439
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:34,720
Today is our happiest day. Like this, come
on.

440
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,520
I don’t understand these moves.

441
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:40,840
I’ll teach you. Come on, a bit more lively.

442
00:50:58,000 --> 00:50:59,400
Nermin.

443
00:51:02,200 --> 00:51:03,200
Nermin!

444
00:51:06,280 --> 00:51:07,280
No.

445
00:51:08,680 --> 00:51:09,680
No.

446
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:11,280
Get me out of here.

447
00:51:12,160 --> 00:51:13,960
Get me out of here!

448
00:51:14,800 --> 00:51:16,120
No.

449
00:51:17,120 --> 00:51:18,120
No.

450
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,440
Are you tired?

451
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:39,280
I wish we were always this tired.
This is the happiest exhaustion of my life.

452
00:51:51,880 --> 00:51:52,880
Excuse me.

453
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:02,280
Is there a problem?

454
00:52:02,800 --> 00:52:05,120
As you can see, everything is in order. No
problems.

455
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:07,960
This calm isn’t a good sign.

456
00:52:08,680 --> 00:52:11,120
You’ve
gotten used to action, to fights, to chaos…

457
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:13,440
So this feels strange to you. Foreign.

458
00:52:14,080 --> 00:52:16,160
But look, everything is under control here.

459
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:20,440
Still, if it
puts your mind at ease, I’ll check around.

460
00:52:22,240 --> 00:52:23,240
I’ll go.

461
00:53:57,720 --> 00:54:01,200
I’ll head inside too.
Fix my hair and makeup.

462
00:54:01,880 --> 00:54:04,880
I don’t want to look messy in photos on my
best day.

463
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:08,640
Let’s slip away. Today is our day.

464
00:54:09,760 --> 00:54:10,960
Yesterday was enough already.

465
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,040
Come.

466
00:55:07,040 --> 00:55:08,040
I’m ready.

467
00:55:12,920 --> 00:55:14,640
I wonder if I’m ready for this beauty.

468
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:19,800
Are you going to say sweet things to me all
day?

469
00:55:21,880 --> 00:55:24,400
Today and for a lifetime after.

470
00:55:33,040 --> 00:55:35,280
I’m the luckiest man in the world.

471
00:55:40,240 --> 00:55:43,560
When you rest your head right here…

472
00:55:44,720 --> 00:55:46,240
I understand what “Ateş” really means.

473
00:55:51,440 --> 00:55:54,040
I’ve never known warmth like your love.

474
00:55:56,240 --> 00:55:57,640
I’m so glad I found you again.

475
00:55:59,960 --> 00:56:02,600
I’m so glad you loved me.

476
00:56:06,600 --> 00:56:07,600
I’ll love you always.

477
00:56:10,960 --> 00:56:11,960
Forever.

478
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:25,040
What if we don’t go, what if we stay here?

479
00:56:27,320 --> 00:56:30,400
The people
downstairs must be waiting, they’ll worry.

480
00:56:30,800 --> 00:56:31,800
Let’s go, come on.

481
00:58:25,360 --> 00:58:29,520
They must be
waiting for the halay. Let’s go join them.

482
00:58:31,680 --> 00:58:32,720
Wait, Mercan.

483
00:58:37,240 --> 00:58:38,280
You forgot this.

484
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:41,000
Thank you.

485
00:59:08,960 --> 00:59:10,600
What’s a wedding without a halay, master?

486
00:59:11,080 --> 00:59:12,960
Play it, let them dance. Come on!

487
01:01:19,040 --> 01:01:21,519
Boys, I think there’s an issue at the back.

488
01:01:21,520 --> 01:01:22,760
Could you check it out?

489
01:01:44,920 --> 01:01:45,920
Where’s Haydar?

490
01:01:49,040 --> 01:01:50,360
Mrs. Müzeyyen…

491
01:01:50,560 --> 01:01:52,600
Haydar is inside, in the basement, waiting
for you.

492
01:01:53,320 --> 01:01:54,320
Didn’t you hear?

493
01:01:56,080 --> 01:01:57,080
What do you mean by that?

494
01:01:57,760 --> 01:01:58,760
Haydar escaped today.

495
01:01:59,480 --> 01:02:01,720
But luckily I had a man inside, they caught
him.

496
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:05,720
Who is that man of yours?

497
01:02:06,320 --> 01:02:09,680
Must you distract me with questions?

498
01:02:10,320 --> 01:02:12,400
I have a lot to do inside.

499
01:03:07,280 --> 01:03:09,520
Your time is up.

500
01:03:10,040 --> 01:03:11,040
Don’t do this, Müzeyyen.

501
01:03:15,240 --> 01:03:18,440
Don’t be Nezir’s pawn.
Don’t join him, there will be bloodshed.

502
01:03:19,480 --> 01:03:20,480
Don’t speak.

503
01:03:21,320 --> 01:03:22,320
Children…

504
01:03:23,040 --> 01:03:25,040
Don’t let our children be sacrificed.

505
01:03:25,280 --> 01:03:26,800
I regret everything, have mercy on me.

506
01:03:27,480 --> 01:03:30,080
You’re the last person
in this world to deserve mercy, Haydar.

507
01:03:35,680 --> 01:03:39,600
Secrets buried in
darkness take lives one day, Haydar.

508
01:03:44,440 --> 01:03:45,880
I came to take yours.

509
01:03:49,480 --> 01:03:50,560
Show mercy.

510
01:03:55,000 --> 01:03:56,120
Have mercy on me!

511
01:03:58,280 --> 01:03:59,280
Mercy?

512
01:04:00,160 --> 01:04:04,120
The day you killed
my husband, you killed the mercy inside me.

513
01:04:08,960 --> 01:04:11,920
Since you stole my son
from me, my heart turned to ice.

514
01:04:17,240 --> 01:04:19,840
You left me longing for the son you took.

515
01:04:20,240 --> 01:04:22,040
You made me the killer of my own child.

516
01:04:26,200 --> 01:04:28,400
Your husband was a thief!

517
01:04:33,280 --> 01:04:34,480
You did this.

518
01:04:34,760 --> 01:04:37,560
You planned everything,
you sent Tahir after me!

519
01:04:38,080 --> 01:04:38,240
You!

520
01:04:39,080 --> 01:04:41,160
Of course I did.

521
